@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About";
}
<h2>@ViewData["Title"].</h2>
<h3>@ViewData["Message"]</h3>

<p>The cost to build a city is @((int) Costs.City).</p>
<p>The cost to build a road is @((int) Costs.Road).</p>
<p>The cost to build a pass is @((int) Costs.Pass).</p>
<p>Moving a unit to a different location is free.</p>
<p>Deleting a unit is free.</p>
<p>When you first register, you will get 1,000 balance from the system.</p>
<p>List View displays all cities, roads and passes in a list format.</p>
<p>You can click Add, Edit, Details or Delete to Create, Update, Read or Delete an item in a text format.</p>
<p>Graphic View displays all cities, roads and passes in a graphic format.</p>
<p>Click an empty cell to create a unit.</p>
<p>Hover on an existing unit, a delete button will appear.</p>
<p>Drag an existing unit to an empty cell to change its position.</p>
<p>Filter View displays all cities, roads and passes in a readonly graphic format.</p>
<p>You can filter the types of units you want to see by check/uncheck the checkboxes on top of the map.</p>
